OU NOT TO TALK ABOUT DOUBLE BOLTS&quot;</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> and soon there is, in your usual eloquent style, a petition to have them placed back into the game based on the following summation from your post.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Conclusion: As long as they are not completely reliable and require skill and opportunity, double bolts are fair and balanced and should be restored, albeit with some modifications to avoid abuse. Bolts spells are inherently tricky to use in the first place, and missed bolts compensate for double bolts. They have been in the game for over three years, and have become a mark of distinction for some of the most dedicated and observant mages, who, as customers, deserve better treatment than a wholesale clipping of a point of pride.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
A <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Point of Pride</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> does not come from <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> exploiting</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> the gaming engine, no more than trading NO-DROP items, or nuking MOBs from places they cannot reach results in a <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  Point of Pride</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.  Unreliable or not, &quot;skill&quot; or not they were not intended to be a part of the spell and were a legitamite bug.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Petitioning</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> for balance through other means such as <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> bolt upgrades</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->, <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> pet enhancements</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->, or other such means is reasonable and I am certain you could make a case for any one of numerous improvements.  However <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> petitioning</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> bugs to be placed <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> in game</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> is not the way to go about it <p><hr>
